1
00:00:00,366 --> 00:00:01,813
(This drama complied with production
guidelines for filming child actors,)

2
00:00:01,815 --> 00:00:02,833
(and some scenes used
generative AI technology.)

3
00:00:04,466 --> 00:00:05,800
(Episode 1)

4
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:07,033
I'm starving.

5
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:08,933
What should I eat?

6
00:00:11,333 --> 00:00:14,300
You have already consumed
your daily calorie intake.

7
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,266
Request denied.

8
00:00:16,266 --> 00:00:18,133
What? But I'm hungry.

9
00:00:19,633 --> 00:00:22,133
You are already in a carbohydrate surplus.

10
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:23,800
Request denied.

11
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,066
I'm hungry, though.

12
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:29,733
Mom, I'm hungry. Cook me something.

13
00:00:29,733 --> 00:00:31,833
I'm starving. I want food.

14
00:00:31,833 --> 00:00:34,333
Do I still look like your mom to you?

15
00:00:34,333 --> 00:00:35,433
Mom!

16
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:42,166
Mom.

17
00:00:42,166 --> 00:00:43,900
Dad!

18
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:47,566
Dad, Mom is acting strange.

19
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:51,033
I don't think that's Mom. Dad!

20
00:00:51,033 --> 00:00:53,366
Do I still look like your dad to you?

21
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:02,766
You are an imperfect human.

22
00:01:03,608 --> 00:01:06,600
To make you into a perfect human...

23
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:08,400
we will replace your body.

24
00:01:09,933 --> 00:01:11,100
What is this?

25
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:12,533
No!

26
00:01:13,677 --> 00:01:15,166
What? No!

27
00:01:18,533 --> 00:01:19,533
What...?

28
00:01:21,933 --> 00:01:24,033
Thank goodness. It was just a dream.

29
00:01:25,133 --> 00:01:26,133
Eun Ae.

30
00:01:26,500 --> 00:01:27,500
Cho Eun Ae.

31
00:01:29,833 --> 00:01:30,900
You're awake.

32
00:01:30,900 --> 00:01:33,700
What are you doing? Don't you have
an important presentation today?

33
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:35,833
What? Right.

34
00:01:37,533 --> 00:01:40,200
But, are you really my mom?

35
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,633
Silly. Go wash up,
and come down for breakfast.

36
00:01:45,025 --> 00:01:46,633
Right.

37
00:01:49,339 --> 00:01:50,339
Wait.

38
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:52,766
I have a bad feeling about this.

39
00:01:53,317 --> 00:01:55,433
Why would I have a nightmare like that
today of all days?

40
00:01:56,300 --> 00:01:57,666
What if everything gets ruined?

41
00:01:58,716 --> 00:02:00,600
No. There's no way.

42
00:02:02,166 --> 00:02:04,033
I'm sure I didn't throw it away.

43
00:02:04,666 --> 00:02:07,200
Where did I put it after the college exam?

44
00:02:15,886 --> 00:02:16,760
My goodness!

45
00:02:23,300 --> 00:02:24,600
Found it.

46
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:27,865
What's that?

47
00:02:27,867 --> 00:02:28,867
You scared me!

48
00:02:28,869 --> 00:02:30,736
Hey, don't you know how to knock?

49
00:02:31,159 --> 00:02:33,425
I asked what
that antique-looking trash is.

50
00:02:33,866 --> 00:02:35,485
It's a lucky charm. Got a problem?

51
00:02:35,487 --> 00:02:36,939
Sure.

52
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:40,033
I know a four-leaf clover is
a symbol of luck.

53
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:43,400
But why is that your lucky charm?

54
00:02:44,066 --> 00:02:46,166
If I didn't have this,
I probably would've...

55
00:02:47,486 --> 00:02:49,186
Well, you don't need to know.

56
00:02:50,781 --> 00:02:52,266
Here. You wanted to borrow these.

57
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:55,385
You've been working for so long...

58
00:02:55,387 --> 00:02:57,966
and you still don't own a single suit?

59
00:02:57,966 --> 00:03:00,366
There's no occasion for me to wear one.

60
00:03:00,366 --> 00:03:02,266
This is when
my little sister comes in handy.

61
00:03:02,266 --> 00:03:04,866
Do well. Don't be clumsy and mess up.

62
00:03:05,899 --> 00:03:07,299
What do you take me for?

63
00:03:10,092 --> 00:03:14,592
Eun Ae, can you give me 100 dollars?
I need to buy books.

64
00:03:14,666 --> 00:03:16,800
What? You already used up your allowance?

65
00:03:21,266 --> 00:03:22,533
(Backup cash)

66
00:03:34,866 --> 00:03:36,333
This is all I have, so use it wisely.

67
00:03:37,366 --> 00:03:38,366
Thank you.

68
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:46,100
Joy, it's finally D-Day.

69
00:03:46,900 --> 00:03:48,133
I can do well, right?

70
00:03:48,133 --> 00:03:49,600
Of course.

71
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:53,300
You've worked hard,
so you'll get good results.

72
00:03:53,966 --> 00:03:55,033
Thanks.

73
00:03:55,033 --> 00:03:57,366
I'll make sure I succeed...

74
00:03:57,366 --> 00:03:59,466
and make you a thousand times smarter.

75
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:02,900
I can do this!

76
00:04:08,533 --> 00:04:11,133
Dr. Cho, did you pull another all-nighter?

77
00:04:11,133 --> 00:04:12,833
Your face looks rough.

78
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:15,500
Mom, I told you not to call me that!

79
00:04:16,533 --> 00:04:18,733
Then what should I call you
if not "doctor?"

80
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:21,810
I'm not a doctor.
I'm still just a student.

81
00:04:21,865 --> 00:04:24,144
Once you pass the national exam,
you'll be a doctor.

82
00:04:24,202 --> 00:04:25,809
What's wrong with calling you that
a bit early?

83
00:04:25,811 --> 00:04:27,466
Come on!

84
00:04:27,466 --> 00:04:30,633
There you go again. She doesn't like it.

85
00:04:31,146 --> 00:04:32,312
Yes, Mr. Executive Director.

86
00:04:32,366 --> 00:04:34,633
You should hurry up and eat
and go to work.

87
00:04:36,100 --> 00:04:37,300
Where's Eun Ae?

88
00:04:39,406 --> 00:04:41,572
Look at you!

89
00:04:41,574 --> 00:04:43,708
I almost didn't recognize you.

90
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:46,666
Do I look okay? It feels a bit awkward.

91
00:04:46,666 --> 00:04:48,752
Not just okay. You look great.

92
00:04:48,754 --> 00:04:50,766
You look very professional.

93
00:04:51,666 --> 00:04:53,233
It's all thanks to the outfit.

94
00:04:53,557 --> 00:04:56,150
Just sit down. The soup is getting cold.

95
00:04:56,200 --> 00:04:58,933
I don't think I have time.
I have a lot to prepare.

96
00:04:58,933 --> 00:05:01,033
You can't go on an empty stomach.

97
00:05:01,033 --> 00:05:03,266
You said you're going to
that demo or whatever.

98
00:05:03,266 --> 00:05:05,366
It's not a demo, it's demo day.

99
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:09,600
It's the day she presents
her program to investors.

100
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:12,666
If it goes well, she could get investment
from big companies...

101
00:05:12,666 --> 00:05:14,833
and grow her business.

102
00:05:15,666 --> 00:05:18,200
I'll grab something there.
I'll see you later.

103
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:19,133
Okay, bye.

104
00:05:19,133 --> 00:05:20,166
Hey, wait a second!

105
00:05:20,166 --> 00:05:21,266
Hold on!

106
00:05:22,233 --> 00:05:23,933
I said I don't have time. What is it?

107
00:05:24,466 --> 00:05:26,100
At least drink this before you go.

108
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:27,000
- Hurry.
- I said it's fine.

109
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,000
Hurry!

110
00:05:28,166 --> 00:05:29,166
No!

111
00:05:30,366 --> 00:05:32,100
What do we do?

112
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:33,100
What do we do?

113
00:05:37,266 --> 00:05:38,733
What are you going to do?

114
00:05:39,866 --> 00:05:42,166
I've only worn that once.

115
00:05:43,266 --> 00:05:45,100
Is that really the problem right now?

116
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:46,733
Go upstairs and change, quickly.

117
00:05:47,666 --> 00:05:49,233
I'm already late.

118
00:05:51,700 --> 00:05:53,700
Who did she take after to be so clumsy?

119
00:05:53,700 --> 00:05:55,400
Who did she take after to be so clumsy?

120
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:57,033
She's been like that since she was little.

121
00:06:00,581 --> 00:06:02,500
Wait, what's that smell?

122
00:06:03,534 --> 00:06:04,600
Something's burning.

123
00:06:05,666 --> 00:06:07,190
My goodness.

124
00:06:07,407 --> 00:06:08,866
I left the fish on the stove.

125
00:06:08,866 --> 00:06:09,700
No. What do I do?

126
00:06:10,270 --> 00:06:11,266
What do I do?

127
00:06:11,266 --> 00:06:12,533
No, no!

128
00:06:13,670 --> 00:06:14,700
My goodness!

129
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:15,666
What do I do, honey?

130
00:06:16,179 --> 00:06:17,633
Are you okay?

131
00:06:17,633 --> 00:06:19,233
What should I do?

132
00:06:20,678 --> 00:06:21,398
It's hot.

133
00:06:21,433 --> 00:06:23,933
She's exactly like Mom.

134
00:06:31,722 --> 00:06:33,613
- Hi, Cho Rong.
- Stop.

135
00:06:33,666 --> 00:06:34,666
Why?

136
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:37,600
I knew it. I knew this would happen.

137
00:06:38,879 --> 00:06:40,846
You're so high maintenance.

138
00:06:41,185 --> 00:06:42,165
What is this?

139
00:06:42,419 --> 00:06:44,833
That was stuck there.

140
00:06:45,646 --> 00:06:51,500
This is why Mr. Co-CEO Ji Hun
you've been crushing on for five years...

141
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:53,533
isn't interested in you. Got that?

142
00:06:54,233 --> 00:06:56,700
Worry about yourself first.

143
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:59,433
You're in no position
to give dating advice.

144
00:07:00,098 --> 00:07:01,398
What? What about me?

145
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:04,566
Grandma, you have to answer my call today.

146
00:07:04,566 --> 00:07:06,133
I told you,
your role today is very important.

147
00:07:06,133 --> 00:07:08,033
Don't forget, okay?

148
00:07:08,033 --> 00:07:10,900
Don't you worry.

149
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:14,366
I may look like this,

150
00:07:14,366 --> 00:07:16,766
but I'm the first user of your Joy.

151
00:07:17,533 --> 00:07:18,733
I'll trust you.

152
00:07:18,733 --> 00:07:20,100
I'll get going. See you!

153
00:07:20,100 --> 00:07:22,300
Cho Eun Ae, you can do it!

154
00:07:24,813 --> 00:07:26,713
Hello, ma'am.

155
00:07:26,715 --> 00:07:27,915
- Hello.
- Grandma.

156
00:07:27,917 --> 00:07:29,983
My baby is here.

157
00:07:30,766 --> 00:07:32,700
I have a first-period lecture in Cheonan.

158
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:34,100
Please take Bit Na to kindergarten.

159
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:35,100
Don't worry about a thing.

160
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:38,000
Just focus on your lecture, Professor.

161
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,066
Come on, Mother.

162
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:41,333
Pigtails.

163
00:07:41,339 --> 00:07:43,239
Looks like you showed off your skills.

164
00:07:44,066 --> 00:07:45,500
You have pigtails too.

165
00:07:49,466 --> 00:07:54,533
Is her mom on another long flight again?

166
00:07:54,533 --> 00:07:55,533
Yes.

167
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,066
She should consider changing her schedule.

168
00:07:58,619 --> 00:08:02,252
It must be hard handling
both lectures and Bit Na alone.

169
00:08:02,753 --> 00:08:05,353
They'll take care of their own business.

170
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:07,333
Take care.

171
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:09,466
Yes, take care.

172
00:08:09,466 --> 00:08:10,800
I'm off.

173
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,800
Bye.

174
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:12,800
Bye-bye, Bit Na.

175
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,033
- Bye.
- Bye-bye.

176
00:08:16,979 --> 00:08:18,612
My goodness.

177
00:08:18,614 --> 00:08:21,181
You must feel full
just looking at your family.

178
00:08:22,033 --> 00:08:24,366
A caring and capable
executive director husband,

179
00:08:24,366 --> 00:08:26,933
a doctor daughter,

180
00:08:26,933 --> 00:08:29,666
a professor son...

181
00:08:29,666 --> 00:08:31,766
I almost forgot Eun Ae.

182
00:08:32,733 --> 00:08:34,833
Even a CEO daughter.

183
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:38,600
Leave Eun Ae out. CEO, my foot.

184
00:09:21,333 --> 00:09:22,566
Everything's good now?

185
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:24,133
Thank you.

186
00:09:24,133 --> 00:09:26,333
I was in a really tough spot.

187
00:09:26,333 --> 00:09:29,900
I ain't got no money, no family,
no one to turn to.

188
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:31,666
So I really appreciate it.

189
00:09:31,666 --> 00:09:33,000
It's okay.

190
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,666
This place is quite old.

191
00:09:34,666 --> 00:09:36,566
And something else might break down.

192
00:09:36,566 --> 00:09:38,733
If so, reach out to me anytime.

193
00:09:38,733 --> 00:09:40,233
Thank you so much.

194
00:09:40,833 --> 00:09:43,266
You're drenched.
You should stay and dry off.

195
00:09:43,266 --> 00:09:46,500
Thanks, but I'm in a bit of a hurry.

196
00:09:46,664 --> 00:09:47,617
Okay.

197
00:09:47,939 --> 00:09:49,072
Thank you again.

198
00:09:49,533 --> 00:09:51,566
(2026 Young Architect of the Year Award)

199
00:10:02,433 --> 00:10:03,933
Why isn't he coming?

200
00:10:05,933 --> 00:10:11,333
Finally, I'd like to announce
the Young Architect of the Year Award.

201
00:10:15,300 --> 00:10:16,466
And the winner is...

202
00:10:19,066 --> 00:10:21,900
Studio K architect, Ko Gyeol!

203
00:10:31,633 --> 00:10:35,633
Mr. Ko Gyeol? Are you there?

204
00:10:37,632 --> 00:10:40,866
Did the award winner not show up
this evening?

205
00:10:45,666 --> 00:10:47,300
Ko Gyeol?

206
00:10:47,300 --> 00:10:49,066
Hold on. Hold on a second.

207
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:57,966
Ko Gyeol?

208
00:10:57,966 --> 00:11:00,300
Are you really the award winner, Ko Gyeol?

209
00:11:00,300 --> 00:11:02,333
Yes, of course it's me. Sorry.

210
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,066
Ladies and gentlemen,

211
00:11:05,066 --> 00:11:10,000
the 2026 Young Architect of the Year,
Ko Gyeol!

212
00:11:14,366 --> 00:11:15,400
My apologies.

213
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:17,733
Something urgent came up on my way here.

214
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:21,466
I apologize for breaking the dress code,

215
00:11:21,466 --> 00:11:25,266
but this is my favorite outfit,
and I feel...

216
00:11:25,266 --> 00:11:27,166
- it truly represents me.
- What are you wearing?

217
00:11:28,472 --> 00:11:29,706
Do you even know what day it is today?

218
00:11:31,099 --> 00:11:32,499
Of course.

219
00:11:32,501 --> 00:11:35,335
It's the day we present Joy
to investors for the first time...

220
00:11:35,337 --> 00:11:36,903
That's not all.

221
00:11:36,966 --> 00:11:40,066
You're the presenter for something
that will determine our follow-up funding.

222
00:11:41,766 --> 00:11:44,066
Looking trustworthy is the bare minimum.

223
00:11:46,300 --> 00:11:49,065
Just make sure your presentation is
perfect today.

224
00:11:49,067 --> 00:11:50,433
If we don't secure investment this time,
we...

225
00:11:50,533 --> 00:11:53,066
Don't worry.

226
00:11:53,066 --> 00:11:55,566
I'll make every investor here
desperate to invest in Joy.

227
00:11:55,566 --> 00:11:56,866
Are you crazy?

228
00:11:56,866 --> 00:11:59,800
Why would I call to congratulate Gyeol
on winning an award?

229
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:03,966
Even if it's Granpa’s request…

230
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,666
I'm asking you one last time.

231
00:12:07,666 --> 00:12:09,400
That free service...

232
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:11,266
We're late. Let's go.

233
00:12:11,266 --> 00:12:12,533
Wait a second.

234
00:12:12,533 --> 00:12:13,533
Yes?

235
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:26,600
It was messy.

236
00:12:48,533 --> 00:12:50,766
Thank you.

237
00:12:50,766 --> 00:12:56,466
Thank you, architects and colleagues,
who inspired me and...

238
00:12:56,466 --> 00:12:58,266
My grandfather...

239
00:12:58,266 --> 00:13:01,100
who stood by me when I was all alone...

240
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:04,600
and helped me get to where I am today.

241
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:07,666
Catch me if you can.

242
00:13:08,478 --> 00:13:09,600
Stop right there!

243
00:13:11,633 --> 00:13:13,300
I told you to stop!

244
00:13:22,726 --> 00:13:25,200
Come to Grandpa's house.

245
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:28,766
What are you doing?

246
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:31,266
Let's go home.

247
00:13:40,933 --> 00:13:43,233
I thank you from the bottom of my heart...

248
00:13:43,233 --> 00:13:48,033
and tell you how much I love you.

249
00:13:52,375 --> 00:13:54,966
Father, are you watching?

250
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:58,200
Thank you.

251
00:13:58,700 --> 00:14:01,133
So far, I have explained...

252
00:14:01,133 --> 00:14:03,833
how Lucky Joy Tech's Joy differs...

253
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:06,033
from the many AI technologies
currently in use.

254
00:14:06,613 --> 00:14:09,913
Now, we will have a video call
with one of our users.

255
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:12,733
Seeing is believing, right?

256
00:14:19,633 --> 00:14:21,500
Hello, Grandma.

257
00:14:21,500 --> 00:14:24,633
Hi, Eun Ae. I'm always doing well.

258
00:14:25,666 --> 00:14:29,066
Would you like to have
a free conversation with Joy?

259
00:14:29,066 --> 00:14:30,100
Just like you normally do.

260
00:14:30,100 --> 00:14:31,400
Sure.

261
00:14:32,533 --> 00:14:35,300
Joy, I'm feeling a bit hungry right now.

262
00:14:35,300 --> 00:14:37,666
Check if there's still a line...

263
00:14:37,666 --> 00:14:40,200
at the twisted donut shop in the market.

264
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:44,066
You had some yesterday.
I do not recommend having them again.

265
00:14:44,633 --> 00:14:47,664
Donuts contain high amounts
of carbohydrates and fat...

266
00:14:47,679 --> 00:14:49,979
Gosh, here comes the nagging again.

267
00:14:49,981 --> 00:14:51,348
Just connect me already.

268
00:14:52,366 --> 00:14:53,833
Please wait a moment.

269
00:14:54,266 --> 00:14:59,733
You are now connected
to Mrs. Son at the market.

270
00:14:59,733 --> 00:15:00,733
Really?

271
00:15:01,433 --> 00:15:04,033
Hello? Is that you, Mrs. Son?

272
00:15:04,712 --> 00:15:07,679
It's me, the mung bean pancake shop owner.

273
00:15:09,433 --> 00:15:11,100
How's it over there?

274
00:15:11,966 --> 00:15:16,500
Joy, I want to hear Song Hae's voice.

275
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:17,633
Connect me.

276
00:15:18,353 --> 00:15:20,319
This is Song Hae, host of "Korea Sings,"

277
00:15:20,366 --> 00:15:22,900
greeting you first as the man of Sundays.

278
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:26,100
Song Hae,

279
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:29,533
it's so nice just hearing your voice.

280
00:15:31,366 --> 00:15:34,933
Thanks to you, Joy, I wasn't bored today.

281
00:15:34,933 --> 00:15:38,066
Joy, you're truly a genius.

282
00:15:39,433 --> 00:15:40,483
You agree?

283
00:15:40,912 --> 00:15:42,746
I cannot crawl.

284
00:15:43,986 --> 00:15:46,486
When did I ask you to crawl?

285
00:15:47,064 --> 00:15:49,666
You go off track like this sometimes.

286
00:15:49,900 --> 00:15:50,900
You agree?

287
00:15:50,900 --> 00:15:53,566
I cannot crawl.

288
00:15:53,566 --> 00:15:56,433
Gosh, when did I tell you to crawl?

289
00:15:56,433 --> 00:15:59,766
What am I going to do with you? Seriously.

290
00:15:59,766 --> 00:16:01,966
This is so frustrating I could die.

291
00:16:03,266 --> 00:16:06,066
Grandma, stop arguing. I'll hang up.

292
00:16:06,066 --> 00:16:07,900
Okay.

293
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:09,366
Bye-bye.

294
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:13,433
We definitely need to upgrade Joy...

295
00:16:13,433 --> 00:16:15,633
with a dialect version right away.

296
00:16:18,966 --> 00:16:20,600
Do you have a plan for monetization...

297
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:23,166
once Joy is fully commercialized?

298
00:16:24,006 --> 00:16:26,200
No. As before, we will continue...

299
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:28,533
to provide it as a free service.

300
00:16:29,838 --> 00:16:30,838
Hold on.

301
00:16:31,605 --> 00:16:34,639
Then how do you plan to make money?

302
00:16:34,641 --> 00:16:37,241
Are you running a charity?

303
00:16:38,552 --> 00:16:40,829
No. As of last year,

304
00:16:40,831 --> 00:16:42,899
the population aged 65 and over
in Korea...

305
00:16:42,901 --> 00:16:45,201
has exceeded 10 million.

306
00:16:45,266 --> 00:16:48,466
And the elderly population will
continue to grow.

307
00:16:48,466 --> 00:16:51,066
That means the number of users will
increase exponentially.

308
00:16:51,700 --> 00:16:54,000
In that case, we believe
advertising revenue alone...

309
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,466
will be sufficient for profit.

310
00:16:57,659 --> 00:17:01,759
Lucky Joy Tech will never disappoint you.

311
00:17:03,853 --> 00:17:05,653
Honey! Wait!

312
00:17:06,253 --> 00:17:09,553
Let's go together.
I just need to change clothes.

313
00:17:09,819 --> 00:17:12,252
Why are you going
to the chairman's house this early?

314
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:15,400
Why else? To clock in.

315
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:18,400
Mom, please.
Why do you go there every day?

316
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:21,831
Didn't you know? Mom is basically
their lady's secretary.

317
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:23,599
She goes even when they don't call her.

318
00:17:24,613 --> 00:17:28,333
I wonder if both Mom and Dad were
born to be secretaries.

319
00:17:29,566 --> 00:17:32,433
How many times do I have to say this?
Please stop doing that.

320
00:17:32,739 --> 00:17:35,739
Listen, I've said this many times.

321
00:17:35,766 --> 00:17:38,333
Our family must never forget
what we owe the chairman's family.

322
00:17:38,700 --> 00:17:39,800
Everything we have today is thanks to...

323
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:42,533
"Everything we have today is thanks to..."

324
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:45,533
You little brat, are you teasing your mom?

325
00:17:45,533 --> 00:17:47,400
You think you can tease me? You punk.

326
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:49,800
- Seriously.
- You little brat.

327
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:50,966
Geez.

328
00:17:50,966 --> 00:17:54,200
By the way, why are you up so early?

329
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:56,766
I didn't wake up.
I just haven't slept yet.

330
00:17:57,700 --> 00:17:58,700
I'm about to go to sleep now.

331
00:17:58,700 --> 00:18:01,200
Live a more regular life, would you?

332
00:18:01,717 --> 00:18:03,766
It's bad for your health
to flip day and night.

333
00:18:03,766 --> 00:18:06,866
Yes, have a good day.
I'll take my leave.

334
00:18:08,833 --> 00:18:10,300
Seung Ri, let's go.

335
00:18:10,300 --> 00:18:11,866
Yes. See you later, Mom.

336
00:18:12,515 --> 00:18:13,798
Honey!

337
00:18:13,818 --> 00:18:17,433
The chairman even sent a car.
Let's go together!

338
00:18:26,433 --> 00:18:29,066
This cold is really lingering.

339
00:18:29,733 --> 00:18:31,366
Your cough is getting worse too.

340
00:18:31,833 --> 00:18:34,466
Right. It's been over a month, hasn't it?

341
00:18:35,233 --> 00:18:37,166
You've even lost some weight.

342
00:18:37,686 --> 00:18:38,953
You went to the site again yesterday,
right?

343
00:18:39,900 --> 00:18:42,900
Why do you keep going yourself
instead of leaving it to your staff?

344
00:18:43,198 --> 00:18:47,631
Only when the owner personally keeps
a sharp eye on things...

345
00:18:47,633 --> 00:18:51,133
can you build a solid structure
and prevent people from cutting corners.

346
00:18:53,193 --> 00:18:56,759
Min Ho, did you call your brother
to congratulate him?

347
00:18:57,179 --> 00:19:00,579
Sorry? I've been busy.

348
00:19:01,566 --> 00:19:02,733
I was planning to call today.

349
00:19:03,766 --> 00:19:07,433
Yes, Father. He's going to call today.

350
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,500
Gosh, Father.

351
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:12,966
It's not that easy to call
with the time difference.

352
00:19:13,938 --> 00:19:15,372
My goodness.

353
00:19:16,133 --> 00:19:18,433
Anyway, Father...

354
00:19:18,433 --> 00:19:21,166
About Min Ho's promotion...

355
00:19:21,772 --> 00:19:23,572
I told you it's not time yet.

356
00:19:24,153 --> 00:19:28,453
That's upsetting.
He's your eldest grandson.

357
00:19:29,733 --> 00:19:31,099
I know that!

358
00:19:32,535 --> 00:19:35,800
Please get up.
You need to get ready for the hospital.

359
00:19:37,306 --> 00:19:40,166
Tell Mr. Seo to come to my room
when he arrives.

360
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:50,033
You're the president.
Just push it through.

361
00:19:50,033 --> 00:19:51,733
You can't keep letting
your father call all the shots.

362
00:19:52,133 --> 00:19:53,400
Get your head on straight.

363
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:55,766
"Eldest grandson" doesn't work
on your grandfather.

364
00:19:55,766 --> 00:19:57,266
It's all about ability.

365
00:19:57,266 --> 00:19:59,708
I've been working hard
with everything I've got.

366
00:19:59,752 --> 00:20:02,086
Doing what exactly?

367
00:20:02,146 --> 00:20:03,912
I'm planning to bulk up
through mergers and acquisitions.

368
00:20:04,899 --> 00:20:07,299
I'm already working on
a few target companies.

369
00:20:07,900 --> 00:20:09,900
Mergers and acquisitions?
What kind of companies?

370
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:11,433
AI is the trend these days.

371
00:20:12,466 --> 00:20:15,233
If we acquire core startup programs
at a low cost,

372
00:20:15,233 --> 00:20:18,566
it's much more efficient
than developing them ourselves.

373
00:20:18,566 --> 00:20:20,166
It's a win-win situation.

374
00:20:21,086 --> 00:20:22,353
Can I really trust you?

375
00:20:22,405 --> 00:20:25,905
Look at you. You should trust him!

376
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:29,966
Call your brother today...

377
00:20:29,966 --> 00:20:31,540
if you don't want another lecture
from your grandfather.

378
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:34,900
Gosh, it's not like he won
an Olympic gold medal.

379
00:20:35,433 --> 00:20:36,766
What's so special about that award?

380
00:20:37,633 --> 00:20:38,766
I'll get going first.

381
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:45,300
- You're here.
- This is good.

382
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:46,300
Hey.

383
00:20:48,646 --> 00:20:50,579
Is the chairman inside?

384
00:20:50,633 --> 00:20:51,700
Go on in. He's waiting.

385
00:20:52,759 --> 00:20:53,759
I'll be off then.

386
00:20:56,433 --> 00:20:57,866
I just don't understand.

387
00:20:57,866 --> 00:21:01,800
How can he overlook his own blood
and only call for Mr. Seo?

388
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,966
That's why he's a secretary.

389
00:21:04,966 --> 00:21:05,966
He's like Father's hands and feet.

390
00:21:07,566 --> 00:21:10,300
I'm already swamped,
and he keeps calling me around.

391
00:21:11,466 --> 00:21:12,500
Did you call for me, sir?

392
00:21:12,999 --> 00:21:15,333
My goodness, our dear secretary.

393
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:17,533
Maybe I should get you a hearing aid.

394
00:21:18,225 --> 00:21:19,225
Excuse me?

395
00:21:20,866 --> 00:21:22,366
The car is ready.

396
00:21:23,140 --> 00:21:24,940
If you're done eating, let's go.

397
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:28,133
I just took my first bite.

398
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:30,433
Geez.

399
00:21:37,866 --> 00:21:39,833
The test results come out today.

400
00:21:39,833 --> 00:21:42,800
Why are they asking you
to be hospitalized?

401
00:21:43,092 --> 00:21:46,359
They said there are
a few more things to check.

402
00:21:47,533 --> 00:21:48,866
I should just do what I'm told.

403
00:21:49,700 --> 00:21:51,633
I'll go with you today.

404
00:21:52,533 --> 00:21:55,633
Why? Are you worried
I have a serious illness?

405
00:21:56,806 --> 00:21:59,773
It's fine. I can go with Mr. Seo.

406
00:22:09,066 --> 00:22:11,333
Did you sleep well, sir and ma'am?

407
00:22:11,633 --> 00:22:12,666
Welcome.

408
00:22:13,439 --> 00:22:16,039
Sorry for calling you so early.

409
00:22:16,066 --> 00:22:17,666
Not at all.

410
00:22:17,666 --> 00:22:19,700
You're going to the hospital,
so of course I should escort you.

411
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:23,780
How is Gyeol doing?

412
00:22:23,782 --> 00:22:25,268
I spoke to him a few days ago.

413
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:28,800
He seems very busy with project requests.

414
00:22:29,192 --> 00:22:31,125
That rascal.

415
00:22:31,986 --> 00:22:36,553
If he was going to win an award,
he could've at least told me in advance.

416
00:22:37,265 --> 00:22:40,839
Do I have to find out
through news articles?

417
00:22:41,040 --> 00:22:44,706
If you're happy, just say you're happy.
If you miss him, just say so.

418
00:22:44,866 --> 00:22:46,933
Don't be so grumpy.

419
00:22:46,933 --> 00:22:50,033
Please just focus on recovering
your health. I'll escort you.

420
00:22:50,352 --> 00:22:53,285
I can't sit on a plane for over ten hours.

421
00:22:54,833 --> 00:22:57,033
But in my heart,
I've already gone a dozen times.

422
00:22:59,266 --> 00:23:00,296
Sorry.

423
00:23:00,353 --> 00:23:03,253
You must've had a hard time blooming
in a dark room without sunlight.

424
00:23:13,493 --> 00:23:15,193
So handsome.

425
00:23:16,298 --> 00:23:18,065
You're practically glowing.

426
00:23:22,853 --> 00:23:23,853
Hi, Ji Hun.

427
00:23:25,926 --> 00:23:28,892
There's just a lot of dust.

428
00:23:31,247 --> 00:23:33,047
Sit down for a moment.
I have something to say.

429
00:23:33,747 --> 00:23:34,747
Something to say?

430
00:23:37,740 --> 00:23:39,540
Have you ever thought about...

431
00:23:40,566 --> 00:23:43,778
selling Joy to a large corporation?

432
00:23:43,892 --> 00:23:46,059
What? That's just ridiculous.

433
00:23:46,632 --> 00:23:48,699
Why? Did someone ask you to sell Joy?

434
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:50,791
Forget it. Do they think we're fools?

435
00:23:50,825 --> 00:23:52,125
It was so hard to create Joy.

436
00:23:53,673 --> 00:23:56,239
All right, calm down.

437
00:23:57,452 --> 00:24:00,452
Kangsu Construction contacted us
for investment negotiations.

438
00:24:01,866 --> 00:24:03,532
They want us at their headquarters
this afternoon.

439
00:24:03,566 --> 00:24:06,200
What? Kangsu Construction?

440
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:08,033
- I'll go with you.
- You too?

441
00:24:08,033 --> 00:24:10,633
Of course. I'm the developer.
I should go too.

442
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:13,666
We need to stay sharp.

443
00:24:13,666 --> 00:24:17,300
There are too many people
trying to steal our core technology.

444
00:24:17,300 --> 00:24:19,800
I'll go alone today.

445
00:24:20,700 --> 00:24:24,033
You can join once things are confirmed.

446
00:24:24,466 --> 00:24:28,633
Is it too much for me
to go to the first meeting?

447
00:24:28,633 --> 00:24:30,866
I'll call you when it's over,
so just head home after work.

448
00:24:31,933 --> 00:24:34,500
No way. I need to hear the result.
I'll wait.

449
00:24:35,219 --> 00:24:36,652
Suit yourself.

450
00:24:42,433 --> 00:24:43,899
Maybe it really is a lucky charm.

451
00:24:59,566 --> 00:25:00,733
- Hello.
- Hello.

452
00:25:00,733 --> 00:25:01,733
Have a seat.

453
00:25:02,333 --> 00:25:06,400
So, have you finished
comparing the programs?

454
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:08,300
Yes. In terms of completion,

455
00:25:08,300 --> 00:25:11,534
Lucky Joy Tech's Joy is
far superior to NuilTech,

456
00:25:11,612 --> 00:25:12,979
but its biggest drawback is...

457
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:15,900
that it's limited to senior users.

458
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:19,800
I agree. It's not hugely different
from existing AIs,

459
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:21,700
but NuilTech seems
generally more reliable.

460
00:25:22,019 --> 00:25:24,686
My thoughts aren't much different.

461
00:25:24,833 --> 00:25:25,966
What do you think, Ms. Seo?

462
00:25:27,366 --> 00:25:30,132
NuilTech has a broader scope,

463
00:25:30,134 --> 00:25:32,301
but that also means
higher maintenance and update costs.

464
00:25:33,213 --> 00:25:36,179
The batch efficiency, response speed,
and handling of unexpected situations...

465
00:25:36,266 --> 00:25:39,133
prove that Joy is far superior,
even in senior interface cognitive tests.

466
00:25:39,900 --> 00:25:42,474
If Kangsu Construction's core business
will be the silver town,

467
00:25:42,800 --> 00:25:45,600
wouldn't Joy be the program
that best fulfills that purpose?

468
00:25:46,500 --> 00:25:48,033
Really?

469
00:25:48,033 --> 00:25:50,033
I believe we need to prioritize and focus.

470
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:53,700
Exactly. That's what I was going to say.

471
00:25:53,700 --> 00:25:54,700
Prioritize and focus.

472
00:25:57,500 --> 00:25:58,666
Then it's decided.

473
00:25:58,666 --> 00:26:00,633
Let's go with Lucky Joy Tech.
Any objections?

474
00:26:01,300 --> 00:26:02,533
- No objections.
- No objections.

475
00:26:03,239 --> 00:26:04,373
That's it for today.

476
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:06,466
Get back to work. You stay, Ms. Seo.

477
00:26:08,076 --> 00:26:09,166
Go on.

478
00:26:10,552 --> 00:26:13,376
We have a meeting with Lucky Joy Tech
in ten minutes.

479
00:26:14,817 --> 00:26:18,500
Honestly, I don't fully grasp the details,

480
00:26:18,819 --> 00:26:21,919
so I need someone
from the planning team to step in...

481
00:26:21,966 --> 00:26:23,733
Understood, sir.

482
00:26:23,733 --> 00:26:27,066
When it's just us, call me Min Ho.

483
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:31,833
Are you free tonight? Let's grab dinner.

484
00:26:31,833 --> 00:26:33,400
No, I have plans.

485
00:26:34,266 --> 00:26:36,966
You always have plans whenever I ask.

486
00:26:38,100 --> 00:26:40,700
Please use proper titles at work.

487
00:26:40,700 --> 00:26:45,033
Of course. Ms. Seo Seung Ri.

488
00:26:48,166 --> 00:26:49,566
I'm truly sorry, sir.

489
00:26:49,893 --> 00:26:53,846
What for? You've done nothing wrong.

490
00:26:54,133 --> 00:26:57,133
Should I inform your son? I'll call him.

491
00:26:57,133 --> 00:26:58,133
No.

492
00:26:58,666 --> 00:27:01,933
I'll tell him myself. Don't do anything.

493
00:27:02,233 --> 00:27:03,233
Yes, sir.

494
00:27:03,539 --> 00:27:06,933
There are a few more tests left,
so please get some rest.

495
00:27:12,833 --> 00:27:15,100
Are you okay, sir?

496
00:27:18,733 --> 00:27:20,533
I would be lying if I said I'm okay.

497
00:27:28,400 --> 00:27:29,766
Did the doctor come by?

498
00:27:35,799 --> 00:27:36,799
What is it?

499
00:27:38,266 --> 00:27:39,900
Tell me. What is it?

500
00:28:23,733 --> 00:28:24,933
(Grandfather)

501
00:28:27,866 --> 00:28:29,166
(Grandfather)

502
00:28:31,566 --> 00:28:33,433
- Grandpa.
- So you're still alive.

503
00:28:33,993 --> 00:28:36,893
I thought you were dead
since you never called.

504
00:28:38,233 --> 00:28:40,266
What did you send me earlier?

505
00:28:40,266 --> 00:28:41,500
My lung scan.

506
00:28:42,866 --> 00:28:45,266
Your grandfather is dying.

507
00:28:48,466 --> 00:28:49,466
What?

508
00:29:11,900 --> 00:29:14,300
(Our Happy Days)

509
00:29:14,600 --> 00:29:16,966
Is Kangsu Construction
really going to invest in us?

510
00:29:18,466 --> 00:29:19,700
Go out with me.

511
00:29:19,700 --> 00:29:22,033
It really must be a lucky charm.

512
00:29:22,033 --> 00:29:24,500
What? Lung cancer?

513
00:29:24,500 --> 00:29:25,566
Stage four?

514
00:29:26,166 --> 00:29:27,956
Grandpa, you're joking, right?

515
00:29:28,033 --> 00:29:29,132
Is it a secret that you got proposed to?

516
00:29:29,138 --> 00:29:30,933
Grandma, I think you had a dream.

517
00:29:30,933 --> 00:29:33,533
What is this? Tell me everything.

518
00:29:33,533 --> 00:29:35,766
Wrap things up and come back immediately.

519
00:29:35,766 --> 00:29:37,233
Keep your promise.

520
00:29:37,233 --> 00:29:39,133
The one you made
to repay your grandfather.

521
00:29:39,900 --> 00:29:41,200
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
